# Project 1. Binary numbers, procedurally

In this project we have a challenge for you: you need to obtain the final board indicated, by
completing the procedures already started.
BUT, you may use only **at most one** built-in procedure in each of the procedures to do.

<center>
![Final board](data:image/png;base64,)
</center>

> **Binary numbers**
>
> Each of the built-in procedures represent what is called a _binary digit_.
> If you draw a table with a column for each of those _digits_, and mark with a 1 when it was used, and with
> a 0 when it was not used, the resulting string of 0s and 1s is called the _binary representation_ of the number.

For example, if you consider the number 19, the table is
 | Number | Drop64Stones | Drop32Stones | Drop16Stones | Drop08Stones | Drop04Stones | Drop02Stones | Drop01Stone |
 |:------:|:------------:|:------------:|:------------:|:------------:|:------------:|:------------:|:-----------:|
 |    19  |       0      |       0      |       1      |      0       |      0       |      1       |      1      |
and so, `0010011` is the binary representation of 19.

Which is the binary representation of each of the numbers you need to drop on the board?
